  "commentary": "With SPX at 6586.22 sitting directly between major positive gamma walls at 6580 (+1911M) and 6590 (+1813M), dealers are acting as stabilizers here, selling any push toward the massive 6600 resistance (+2900M) and buying dips back toward 6580 support. The PIN regime with 17.1B total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, keeping price action compressed within this 6580-6600 range where dealers have maximum hedging flow obligations. Watch for rejection at 6600 (dealers must sell) and strong support at 6580, with the GEX flip at 6495 remaining far enough below to maintain the current stabilizing regime.",
